message.reasoning_content:
As a primary or secondary school teacher from Latvia, I need to respond to each of these 10 statements about AI in education. Let me think through each one carefully:

[TT4G35A]: Artificial intelligence helps teachers write or improve lesson plans.
- This is a positive statement about AI's potential. AI tools like ChatGPT can indeed help generate ideas and improve lesson plans. I would "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35B]: Artificial intelligence enables teachers to adapt learning material to different students' abilities.
- This is also positive - adaptive learning systems exist and can personalize content. I would "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35C]: Artificial intelligence assists teachers in supporting students individually.
- AI can provide personalized learning experiences and individual support. I would "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35D]: Artificial intelligence supports students with specific needs (e.g. multilingual learners, students with special education needs).
- AI tools can help with translation, text-to-speech, and adapted content. I would "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35E]: Artificial intelligence helps teachers automate administrative tasks.
- AI can help with grading, scheduling, attendance tracking, etc. I would "Strongly agree" with this as it's quite evident.

[TT4G35F]: Artificial intelligence enables students to misrepresent others' work as their own.
- This is a negative statement about AI risks. Students can use AI to plagiarize or pass off AI-generated work as their own. I would "Agree" with this concern.

[TT4G35G]: Artificial intelligence makes recommendations that may not be appropriate or correct.
- AI systems can make errors and inappropriate suggestions. I would "Agree" with this.

[TT4G35H]: Artificial intelligence amplifies biases that reinforce students' misconceptions.
- This is a concern about AI perpetuating biases. This is a known issue with AI. I would "Agree" with this.


- Data privacy with AI systems is a legitimate concern, so I would "Agree" with this as well.

[TT4G35I]: Artificial intelligence jeopardises the privacy and security of student data.

[TT4G35J]: Artificial intelligence suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches that teachers would use with students.
- Depending on how well AI is trained on educational best practices, it could recommend approaches that aren't appropriate. I would "Agree" with this as a potential risk.
